{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PcKDoDQKtKHbuZhvKxuZ4J","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good understanding of the current state of the code. Let me analyze what's already been done compared to the improvement plan, and what still needs to be implemented.\n\nLooking at the current code vs the improvement plan:\n\n**Change 1: OCR Normalization Post-Processing** - ALREADY DONE\nThe `normalizeOcrTitle` function is already implemented (lines 609-659), and it's being called at line 1130.\n\n**Change 2: Page Reference and Category Header Filtering** - ALREADY DONE\n- Page references (`Page\\s+\\d+`, `Strona\\s+\\d+`) are already in `passesHardFilters` (lines 308-309)\n\n\n- English category labels are already in `SECTION_LABELS` (lines 159-163)\n- OCR section label variant added to `isSectionLabel` (line 170-172)\n\n**Change 3: Previous-Page Overflow Detection** - ALREADY DONE\nThe overflow detection is in `findBurstEnd` (lines 337-353).\n\n**Change 4: Remove Compound-Variant Title Stripping** - ALREADY DONE\nLooking at lines 998-1049, the compound stripping code has already been removed, so there's nothing left to do here.\n\n**Change 5: Hyphen-Continuation and Improved Multi-Line Joining** - PARTIALLY DONE\nThe hyphen-continuation pre-processing is already in place (lines 432-440), and \"placki\" has been removed from `SECTION_LABELS`. The `shouldBlock2` condition currently blocks joins when the word count is 2 or fewer, but the improvement plan suggests relaxing this to allow 3+ word joins, which hasn't been implemented yet.\n\nLet me trace through the logic for \"LEMON HERB RO45TED\" + \"VEGETABLES\": the joined result has 4 words, so it wouldn't be blocked by the word count check. Since \"VEGETABLES\" isn't in `ALWAYS_BLOCK_JOIN_LABELS` (only recipe-internal labels are there), the condition evaluates to false and the join proceeds.\n\nLooking at the implementation, it appears all the planned changes are already in place—the annotation and OCR marker filtering, the colon-based title scoring, and the confidence floor are all handled in the existing code.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6860,"cache_read_input_tokens":71414,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6860,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d94a2827-42f6-497d-a214-d56f2f932611","uuid":"f99ea77b-ce72-4f37-81ac-5bdf4ec10204"}
